cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.CV

The paper deals with learning-based motion control for autonomous systems, which involves machine learning (ML) techniques such as Gaussian process (GP) regression. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also focuses on motion control, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes a model predictive control (MPC) method, which is a control theory technique, and hence, it can be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also deals with safety issues, which is a critical aspect of autonomous systems, and hence, it can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses a nonlinear car-like vehicle model for simulations, which involves computer vision techniques, and hence, it can be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
